# Rust
/target

# Scanner test fixtures are NOT committed. A corpus holding one valid-looking secret per
# rule is, by design, indistinguishable from real credentials, so committing it trips
# GitHub secret-scanning push protection. The full-ruleset test generates its corpus at
# runtime instead -- see generated_corpus() in src/scanner.rs. This keeps the repository
# free of any detectable secret.
tests/fixtures/
secrets_test.env
.flashaudit_state.json

